      "rationale": "RH index: mean absolute percent error 9.7% across 5 operating points. Pump head: mean error 4.3%. Velocity magnitude (PIV): spatial correlation 0.91. All metrics satisfy the 15% threshold. Gradation 2 achieved. Note: comparisons performed exclusively under laminar-regime test conditions; turbulent shear stress contribution to hemolysis not compared."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "RH < 1 is the regulatory acceptance criterion for predicate comparison. The model outputs RH directly via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage accumulation integral applied along Lagrangian particle paths. QoI is clinically and regulatorily relevant. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, flow rates, and blood analogue are representative of CPB operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry used for both simulation and in-vitro testing. Operating points span 2–6 L/min at 2500–4500 RPM, covering the intended CPB clinical range. Bovine blood used as analogue. Validation activities are representative of COU at Gradation 2. Turbulent-regime conditions above 4500 RPM are outside the validated test matrix and are not addressed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to residual tolerance of 1e-5 for all transport equations.",
      "rationale": "All steady-state simulations converged to mass and momentum residuals below 1e-6. Species transport residual below 1e-5. Convergence plots archived. Gradation 1 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material properties verified against COU specification.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup completed by second qualified CFD analyst. Boundary condition checklist signed off. No discrepancies identified. Gradation 1 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations and constitutive models documented; simplifying assumptions stated.",
      "rationale": "Steady-state incompressible Navier-Stokes equations solved with laminar flow assumption throughout. Non-Newtonian blood viscosity represented by Carreau-Yasuda model. Hemolysis accumulation via Giersiepen-Wurzinger model. Model form documented in simulation report SR-2024-07. Turbulent fluctuations are not modelled; the model description notes 'simplified laminar flow assumption applied uniformly' without quantifying the impact of turbulence exclusion on RH predictions. No fidelity trade study comparing laminar versus turbulence-resolved results has been conducted. Gradation 2 formally met on documentation criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters traceable to measurement or published reference; uncertainty in key inputs (viscosity, haematocrit) quantified.",
      "rationale": "Viscosity parameters fit to rheometry data (R²=0.98). Haematocrit 33% nominal with ±2% uncertainty propagated via two additional simulations. Hemolysis model constants from Giersiepen et al. (1990) as published. Input traceability matrix completed. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
